        <div class="content-body">
          <p>International universities have strict documentation requirements, and even a small error or missing item can delay or derail your application. Grant Consulting provides a thorough review of every academic and personal document you need to submit — transcripts, diplomas, recommendation letters, personal statements, and standardized test scores — to make sure everything is complete, accurate, and properly formatted.</p>
          <p>Transcript evaluation is a critical part of applying to universities abroad, especially when your academic records follow a different grading system. We assess your transcripts against the standards of your target country and institution, calculate GPA equivalencies where needed, and identify any courses or credits that may require additional explanation or supplementary documentation.</p>
          <p>Our document review process also includes a gap analysis that highlights anything missing from your application package before you submit. Whether it is an outdated test score, a missing notarized translation, or a recommendation letter that does not meet the university's format requirements, we catch these issues early so you have time to address them without jeopardizing your deadlines.</p>
        </div>

